03/04/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian police said Thursday (April 2nd) it arrested 42 people on suspicion of having smuggled nearly 200 illegal migrants to Western European countries.
It conducted the operation to dismantle the human trafficking ring in co-operation with police from Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH), Slovenia and Austria.
The traffickers smuggled illegal immigrants across Turkey, Serbia, Montenegro, Macedonia, BiH, Croatia and Slovenia into Austria and further to other EU countries.
(HINA, Jutarnij List, Xinhua, UPI, STA - 02/04/09)
